definition.val: Measuring the diameter of any object.
Measurement of any size.
Observing a sample by electron microscopy.
Assessing the timing of fruiting body development.
In a micropipette chemotaxis assay, typically cAMP is in the micropipette and moving the tip around cells keep turning towards the source.
Agglutination is the clumping of cells, in Dictyostelium e.g. the ampA gene plays a role in cell agglutination during growth.
Phalloidin is often conjugated with a dye to label for example actin.
Testing the attachment of cells to plastic.
A gene is marked by any stain or label and observed by microscopy.
THe measurement of any surface such as an agar plate or a glass slide.
After protein electrophoresis and generating a blot, visualizing target protein using a primary and secondary antibody.
The objective of FACS is to physically sort a heterogeneous cell sample, one labeled fluorescent the other  not labeled, into separate populations.
After separation of proteins by electrophoresis a blot is generated and stained with antibodies.
High throughput microscopy is a powerful tool to analyze cellular dynamics requiring automated processing; this is dark field microscopy.
In situ hybridization is a  technique in which a single-stranded DNA or RNA sequence (a probe) is allowed to form complementary base pairs with DNA or RNA present in a tissue.
High throughput microscopy is a powerful tool to analyze cellular dynamics requiring automated processing; this is bright field microscopy.
Observing a sample by dark field microscopy.
Observing a sample by bright field microscopy.
Observing a sample by fluorescence microscopy.
Using any stain to mark a sample.
Observing a sample by reflection interference contrast microscopy.
Observing a sample by confocal microscopy.
Creating an attractant gradient to test cell motility towards this source.
Testing competent cells in a chemotaxis chamber.
The Dictyostelium slug can be transplanted and grafted and positioned cell types de-differentiate.
Chimeric cell mixtures often result in abnormal kin recognition and cell population might segregate during development.
In 2D electrophoresis, first proteins are separated by the pI (soelectric point) value and second  by their relative molecular weight.
In immunoprecipitation  (IP) a protein is bound by a specific antibody that is often immobilized on beads and thus purified from a solution of different proteins.
In biochemical fractionation cells or enriched parts of cells are separated into proteins or complexes by centrifugation using a dense gradient.
The combination of sodium dodecyl sulfate (SDS) and polyacrylamide gel eliminates the influence of structure and charge, and proteins are separated solely by their molecular weight.

synonyms.val: sodium dodecyl sulphate polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis

definition.val: Agarose overlay of cells under a thin agarose sheet to slightly flatten the cells and keeping them moist during microscopy.
Observing a sample by phase contrast microscopy.
Testing cells for the phagocytosis of FITC-dextran.
Testing cells for the phagocytosis of polystyrene particles.
Observing a sample by differential interference contrast microscopy.
Testing cells for the phagocytosis of TRITC-dextran.
PCR allows the amplification of trace DNA samples into massive copies using specific primers.
Used to amplify RNA targets; the RNA template is converted into cDNA by the enzyme reverse transcriptase and the cDNA serves as a template for amplification using PCR.
Beta-galactosidase staining is used on fixed specimen.
In a monolayer culture cells do not overlap and are not too dense but form an even lawn.
Observing a sample by total internal reflection fluorescence microscopy.
Testing the phagocytosis rate of cells.
The prestalk region of the Dictyostelium slug stains strongly with neutral red.
Counting spores in disrupted spore heads.
Investigating samples by any kind of microscopy.
Measuring growth rate and investigating development time and quality.
Spore viability is often tested with detergent treatment, or germination experiments.
Observing quality and timing of fruiting body development.
Early development submerged in buffer.
Calcofluor white stains cellulose; the Dictyostelium stalk contains cellulose.
Beta-glucoronidase staining is used on fixed specimen.
Electrophoresis separates molecules and a blot on a membrane may be generated.
Any analysis of a large scale experiment.
Investigating or testing any step in microRNA processing.
RNA-Seq uses next-generation sequencing to reveal the presence and quantity of RNA in a biological sample at a given moment.
Any study to determine gene expression.
Determining the efficiency of homologous recombination.
Determining the efficiency of a transformation assay.
Determining the efficiency of restriction enzyme mediated transformation.

definition.val: Mass spectrometry is an analytical tool useful for measuring the mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) of one or more molecules present in a sample.
Testing the adhesion of cells to a substrate.
Propidium iodide staining is often used to determine cell death in Dictyostelium.
Development submerged in buffer.
During time-lapse microscopy a picture is automatically taken in specific time intervals.
Measurement of any ion concentration intra- or extracellular.
Real-time PCR combines PCR amplification and detection into a single step; for quantification of the PCR product an intercalating dye or a hydrolysis-based probe is commonly used.
Centrifugation separates components in a tube by size and / or weight.

Spores may be induced to germinate by heat shock or DMSO treatment, axenic strain spores germinate also in HL5 medium; in nature and lab spores germinate when sensing folate from bacteria that serve as food,.
Counting the cells typically using a hemocytometer.
Testing the attachment of cells to glass.
Any biochemical assay.
Observing quality and timing of early development.
Represents any assay performed in the Dictyostelium field.
The amount of SDF-1 is determined during development.
A protein is purified from any cell mass or separated cell part.
Dictyostelium produces SDF-1 and SDF-2 and the SDF assay determines how much SDF is needed for sporulation.
Observing and measuring slug motility.
The amount of any secreted signaling or other molecule may be measured.
Intracellular determination of any molecule concentration or amount of interest.
The amount of SDF-2 is determined during development.
Testing if cells are viable and propagate.
Testing cells for the phagocytosis of yeast particles.
After separating RNA molecules by electrophoresis a blot is generated followed by hybridization with complimentary DNA.
Radio immune assay measures the presence of an antigen with very high sensitivity using an antibody to the antigen labeled with a radioisotope.
Testing cells for the phagocytosis of latex beads.
Taken samples during growth to count cells leads to the growth curve.
The component of interest in the sample is labeled with an antibody tagged with a fluorescent marker and observed with a fluorescence microscope.
Observing and measuring the motility of cells or the slug.
Dictyostelium plaques are count on a bacterial lawn, each plaque when diluted enough represents decendants from a single cell.
Counting the nuclei in a cell typically by DAPI staining.

basicPropertyValues.val: A structured controlled vocabulary of various assays of the slime-mold Dictyostelium discoideum.
